title: Former NSW Premier Mike Baird joins National Australia Bank | Daily Telegraph
text:
Former NSW Premier Mike Baird joins National Australia Bank The Daily Telegraph February 28, 2017 8:48am 
FORMER NSW premier Mike Baird is joining National Australia Bank as chief customer officer for the lender’s corporate and institutional banking unit. 
Mr Baird retired unexpectedly from politics in January to spend more time with his family. media_camera Mike Baird with his successor Gladys Berejiklian. 
NAB’s statement to the Australian Securities Exchange says Mr Baird, who previously worked for the bank, will take up his new job in April. 
The 48-year old had been Liberal premier since April 2014 and said when he retired that he wanted to spend time with his family and to help his parents and sister through “serious health challenges”. 
“His time as treasurer and premier of New South Wales means he returns to banking and NAB with invaluable experience in leading economic and financial reform to grow the economy,” NAB CEO Andrew Thorburn said of Mr Baird. 
“Mike has outstanding leadership and a determination to drive change and make a difference by building relationships with customers and the community.”
